{% extends "base.html.j2" %}
{% block title %}Manual Apply &mdash; Job Apply{% endblock %}
{% block content %}
<h2>Manual Apply</h2>
<p>Paste a job URL (Greenhouse, Lever, Ashby, or generic) to add it to the review queue.
The job bypasses the keyword-match threshold but still respects duplicate detection
and the standard tailoring + submission pipeline.</p>

<form hx-post="/manual-apply/preview"
      hx-target="#preview-slot"
      hx-swap="innerHTML"
      hx-indicator="#preview-spinner">
  <fieldset role="group">
    <label for="manual-apply-url" style="flex: 1;">
      Job URL
      <input id="manual-apply-url"
             type="url"
             name="url"
             placeholder="https://boards.greenhouse.io/acme/jobs/1234"
             required>
    </label>
  </fieldset>
  <button type="submit">Preview</button>
  <span id="preview-spinner" class="htmx-indicator">Fetching...</span>
</form>

<div id="preview-slot"></div>

<hr>
<details>
  <summary>Can't fetch a job URL? Paste the description manually.</summary>
  <p>If a URL is behind an auth wall (LinkedIn, Indeed) or otherwise fails to load,
  the preview step will automatically swap to a fallback form. You can also kick off
  the fallback form directly with a bogus URL.</p>
</details>
{% endblock %}
